[KevlarNVGoggles]
Description=The PASGT (Personnel Armor System for Ground Troops) Level IIIA kevlar helmet has been used by law-enforcement agencies and military units alike from around the world for decades. The PASGT helmet provides protection from hollow point rounds, most forms of buckshot, shotgun slugs and small caliber full metal jacket rounds. However, it can't stop rifle caliber rounds or armor piercing pistol ammunition. The PVS-7 Night Vision Goggles work by amplifying available light and allow the wearer to see in dark areas. Due to their lack of color and limited field of vision, the goggles can make it more difficult to distinguish friend from foe.
